DataElement.preferredDefinition: A type of evaluation that is primarily descriptive and interpretative, and may or may not lend itself to quantification. Mainly concerned with the properties, the state, and the character (i.e., the nature) of phenomena. It implies an emphasis on processes and meanings that are rigorously examined, but not measured in terms of quantity, amount, or frequency. (www.unfpa.org/monitoring/toolkit/glossary.pdf and Nonprofit Good Practice Guide Glossary)_Systematic, objective appraisal of the significance, effectiveness, and impact of activities or condition according to specified objectives and criteria.:The particular day, month and year an event will happen or has happened._Generic value domain for a java datatype that represents a specific instant in time, with millisecond precision.
